What is ISO20022, and why is it important in T24 payments?
A12:
ISO20022: A universal standard for financial messages in XML.
Used for cross-border payments, enabling rich remittance data.
T24 maps ISO20022 fields into internal OFS structures for processing.

WIFT: Cross-border, uses MT/MX formats. T24 integrates via SWIFTNet.
ACH/FPS: Domestic clearing (batch/real-time). ACH uses NACHA standards, FPS is real-time settlement.



